To evaluate the derivative of a multivariable function g = g(x,y) with
respect to t where x,y are functions of t, we need to use the chain rule
for multivariable functions:

\begin{align*}\frac{dg}{dt} = \frac{\partial g}{\partial x}\frac{dx}{dt} + \frac{\partial g}{\partial y}\frac{dy}{dt} = g_{x}\frac{dx}{dt} + g_{y}\frac{dy}{dt}.\end{align*}
